data.enText: to initiate legal proceedings against sb

data.chText: 政府已开始实施经济改革方案。
data.enText: The government has initiated a programme of economic reform.

data.chText: 使了解；传授；教…开始尝试
data.enText: to explain sth to sb and/or make them experience it for the first time

data.chText: 他们中有很多人在早年就被教会了吸毒。
data.enText: Many of them had been initiated into drug use at an early age.

data.chText: （尤指在秘密仪式上）使加入，接纳，吸收
data.enText: to make sb a member of a particular group, especially as part of a secret ceremony

data.chText: 每年有好几百人被接纳到这个教派中。
data.enText: Hundreds are initiated into the sect each year.

data.chText: 新加入某组织（或机构、宗教）的人；新入会的人
data.enText: a person who has been allowed to join a particular group, organization, or religion and is learning its rules and secrets

simple_means.memory_skill: in 使… + it 行走 + iate 做 → 使行走〔起来〕→ 开始

means: (尤指在秘密仪式上)使加入，接纳，吸收
新加入某组织(或机构、宗教)的人

tr: people who have been introduced to the mysteries of some field or activity
example: it is very familiar to the initiate

tr: someone who has been admitted to membership in a scholarly field
someone new to a field or activity
set in motion, start an event or prepare the way for
example: Hitler's attack on Poland led up to World War II

tr: bring up a topic for discussion
take the lead or initiative in
example: This South African surgeon pioneered heart transplants

tr: accept people into an exclusive society or group, usually with some rite
example: African men are initiated when they reach puberty

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /ɪ'nɪʃieɪt/. The noun is pronounced /ɪ'nɪʃiət/. 动词读作 /ɪ'nɪʃieɪt/。名词读作 /ɪ'nɪʃiət/。

value.def: If you initiate something, you start it or cause it to happen.

example.ex: They wanted to initiate a discussion on economics...
example.tran: 他们想启动一次经济学讨论。

example.ex: The trip was initiated by the manager of the community centre.
example.tran: 这次旅行由社区活动中心的经理发起。

value.def: If you initiate someone into something, you introduce them to a particular skill or type of knowledge and teach them about it.

example.ex: He initiated her into the study of other cultures.
example.tran: 他将她领进了研究其他文化的大门。

value.tran: 使初步了解;向…传授基本技巧(或基础知识)

value.def: If someone is initiated into something such as a religion, secret society, or social group, they become a member of it by taking part in ceremonies at which they learn its special knowledge or customs.

example.ex: In many societies, young people are formally initiated into their adult roles.
example.tran: 在很多社会里,年轻人经过正式仪式才算成年。

example.ex: ...the ceremony that initiated members into the Order.
example.tran: 吸收成员加入会社的仪式

value.def: An initiate is a person who has been accepted as a member by a particular group or club and been taught its secrets and skills.

example.ex: Chen was an initiate of a Chinese spiritual discipline.
example.tran: 陈是某个中国神学领域的新入门者。

value.tran: 有初步知识的成员;新入会的人
